Air Quality Monitoring Network

SebaYMF
March-2015

The Macam Network

The air quality monitoring network (Macam) is a group of eleven automatic stations capable of register the concentration of six fundamental parameters of the air quality:

  • Particulate matter < 2,5 um (PM2,5)
  • Particulate matter < 10 um (PM10)
  • Carbon Monoxide (CO)
  • Ozone (O3)
  • Nitrogen Dioxide (NO2)
  • Sulfur Dioxide (SO2)

Time series analisys

With our shiny app stored in the shinyapps web you can perform a complete analisys of the variation of the concentration of PM2,5 in Santiago city (Chile) in the last 24 hours. Using the interactivity from the shiny package you can select between compare the data from the stations all thogether, or into separate graphs.

Spacial distribution

Using ggplot2 package it is easy to add diferents layers to the map, and with the geoR package it is possible to perform a interpolation between the data stations. 

ggplot(...,aes(...))+geom_tile(..., aes(...))+geom_polygon(...,aes(...))+ geom_point(...,aes(...))
